'''The onion router''', or [::Tor], is a software package that allows you to use an anonymity network to keep secret the details of your Internet activity.
* http://www.torproject.org/
* [[WikiPedia:Tor (anonymity network)]]
* [https://wiki.torproject.org/noreply/TheOnionRouter TorProject:TheOnionRouter]
[[Anonymous]] editors of the Wiki can use this tool to keep their IP address secret.  See UserName for more information.
== Tor and vc ==
If you wish to route all vc (VersionControl) through tor, set vc-tor to t.
== eww ==
[[eww]] e.g.\\
<code>HTTPTunnelPort 9999</code>\\
<code>(setopt url-proxy-services '(("https" . "localhost:9999") ("http" . "localhost:9999") ("no_proxy" . "^\\(.*\\.\\)?example\\.com$")))</code>
== Gnus ==
[[Gnus]] e.g.\\
<code>(setq gnus-secondary-select-methods '((nnimap "Example" (nnimap-address "imap.example.com") (nnimap-server-port 993) (nnimap-shell-program "torsocks openssl s_client -connect %s:%p -quiet") (nnimap-stream shell))))</code          >
